document_data.History:
In his youth, Rathloff was a sailor. When he went to Tarmalune during his travels, he met [[Halagothra]] and both fell in love. They married soon after. However, when she bore him a son, Halagothra left and he never saw her again. When his son died of plague in [[1471 DR]], Rathloff took care of his granddaughter, [[Glindarra]]. 

In 1479 DR, Rathloff helped a band of [[adventurer]]s that were investigating the activities of the Cult of Reborn Flame in Ramekho.{{Cite organized play/LFR/Quench the Fire of the Raging God|48}}

Rathloff became obsessed with the primordial Cirotralech and his consort, the [[titan]]ess known as the [[Bride]].{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|26}} He took leadership of a primordial cult known as the [[Sons of Winter]], and went to Fimbrul to use Pyrultimus' ritual to awaken Cirotralech and the Bride.

The adventurers, who considered him their friend,{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|36}}
